==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} '''bulla''', bubble.

===Noun===
{{Wikipedia}}
'''bulla''' ''(plural '''bullae''', adj. '''bullous''')''

# {{medicine}} A [[blister]], [[vesicle]], or other thin-walled cavity or [[lesion]].
# {{cattag|Archaeology}} A clay envelope or hollow ball, typ. with seal impressions or writing on its outside indicating its contents.
# In ancient Rome, a kind of [[amulet]] or [[boss]].
# Later, handwrited document from the papal chancellery.